  "content": "## Docs Workflow Implementation Status (2026-03-16)\n\n### Phase 1: Metadata + Repo-Aware Write + Filtered Search — COMPLETE\n\nAll tasks done. EntryMetadata has content_role/source_origin fields. DocsConfig/DocsRulesConfig structs exist. RetrievalOpts post-filter works. MCP tools (search/write/context) accept filter params. Ingestion pipeline now auto-populates content_role (inferred from directory: rfcs→design, plans→plan, decisions→decision, learnings→learning, code extensions→code, AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md→instruction) and source_origin (repo:corvia for repo files, workspace for docs/ files). Workspace docs/ directory is now ingested (decisions, learnings, marketing, plans). Basic adapter walk_dir fixed to preserve subdirectory paths. 4,643 total chunks indexed (4,124 repo + 519 workspace).\n\nKey files changed: workspace.rs (infer_content_role, infer_source_origin, workspace docs ingest block), basic adapter main.rs (walk_dir root param fix), main.rs (single-path ingest metadata).\n\n### Phase 2: Dashboard Graphed Document Reader — NOT STARTED\n\n- Add content_role/source_origin to dashboard TypeScript types\n- New DocumentReader.tsx side panel (entry content + metadata badges)\n- New NeighborCards.tsx (clickable related entries for graph traversal)\n- New GraphControls.tsx (depth slider, role/origin filter dropdowns)\n- Refactor GraphView.tsx to split-panel layout with entry-level graph\n- New REST endpoint: GET /api/dashboard/entries/{id}/neighbors\n\n### Phase 3: Intelligence (Reasoner + Docs Check) — NOT STARTED\n\n- Add MisplacedDoc, TemporalContradiction, CoverageGap check types to Reasoner\n- Implement the three check functions\n- Add `corvia workspace docs check` CLI subcommand\n- Dashboard: render new finding types in HealthPanel\n\n### Phase 4: Enforcement (Hooks + Git Triggers) — ~40% DONE\n\nDone: doc-placement-check.sh hook, CLAUDE.md instructions, corvia.toml blocked_paths, hooks.rs generation.\nRemaining: --incremental/--files ingest implementation (args exist but stubbed), init-hooks CLI subcommand, git post-commit hooks, .claude/settings.json auto-merge.",
